{{> header.mustache }}
<div class="row">
    <section class="col-lg-12">
        <div class="box box-default">
            <div class="box-header with-border">
                <h3 class="box-title">What are these settings?</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="box-body">
                With these settings you can modify the general configuration for the bot, e.g. how commands are ran,
                and which channels it is allowed talk in.
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>
<div class="row">
    <section class="col-lg-4 col-sm-12">
        <div class="box box-default">
            <div class="box-header with-border">
                <h3 class="box-title">Command prefix</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="box-body">
                <p>This is what character is used to run commands, e.g. <code>!help</code>, where the prefix is
                    <code>!</code> and the command is <code>help</code>.</p>
                <form>
                    <div class="form-group">
                        <label for="channel">Channel</label>
                        <select class="form-control" id="channel">
                            <option>#general (current: @Genie)</option>
                            <option>#shitpost (current: !)</option>
                            <option>#testing (current: $)</option>
                            <option>#info (current: !)</option>
                        </select>
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-group">
                        <label for="channel">Prefix Character</label>
                        <input type="text" placeholder="Prefix character" id="prefix" class="form-control">
                    </div>
                    <button type="submit" class="btn btn-default btn-block">Save</button>
                </form>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section class="col-lg-4 col-sm-12">
        <div class="box box-default">
            <div class="box-header with-border">
                <h3 class="box-title">Enabled Channels</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="box-body">
                <p>
                    These are the channels that the bot is active in. If you disable a channel, the bot will not
                    respond to any commands or messages in that channel.<br /><br />
                    If the bot does not have permission to talk in that channel anyway (e.g. discord role), these
                    settings will not matter.
                </p>
            </div>
            <table class="table table-hover table-bordered table-responsive">
                <tr>
                    <th>Name</th>
                    <th>Status</th>
                    <th></th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>
                        <a href="#">#general</a>
                    </td>
                    <td>Disabled</td>
                    <th style="text-align: center">
                        <a href="#"><div class="btn btn-success btn-block btn-xs">Enable</div></a>
                    </th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>
                        <a href="#">#shitpost</a>
                    </td>
                    <td>Enabled</td>
                    <th style="text-align: center">
                        <a href="#"><div class="btn btn-danger btn-block btn-xs">Disable</div></a>
                    </th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>
                        <a href="#">#testing</a>
                    </td>
                    <td>Enabled</td>
                    <th style="text-align: center">
                        <a href="#"><div class="btn btn-danger btn-block btn-xs">Disable</div></a>
                    </th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>
                        <a href="#">#info</a>
                    </td>
                    <td>Disabled</td>
                    <th style="text-align: center">
                        <a href="#"><div class="btn btn-success btn-block btn-xs">Enable</div></a>
                    </th>
                </tr>
            </table>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section class="col-lg-4 col-sm-12">
        <div class="box box-default">
            <div class="box-header with-border">
                <h3 class="box-title">Verbose</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="box-body">
                <p>
                    These settings are related to the help and error messages the bot sends. You may wish to
                    enable/disable these as some of these messages can be quite spammy or unnecessary.
                </p>
                <form>
                    <div class="checkbox">
                        <label>
                            <input type="checkbox" id="invalidCommandMessage" aria-describedby="invalidCommandHelp"> Invalid command message
                        </label>
                        <span id="invalidCommandHelp" class="help-block">
                            This message is shown when an invalid command is ran. For example, if <code>!waufhwa</code>
                            is ran but is not a command, the bot will say back "Invalid command!"
                        </span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="checkbox">
                        <label>
                            <input type="checkbox" id="noPermissionMessage" aria-describedby="noPermissionHelp" checked> No permission message
                        </label>
                        <span id="noPermissionHelp" class="help-block">
                            This message is shown when a user runs a command but they aren't allowed to due to their
                            role on the network.
                        </span>
                    </div>
                    <button type="submit" class="btn btn-default btn-block">Save</button>
                </form>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>
{{> footer.mustache }}
